Ifeanyi Onuba, Abuja The Minister of Industry, Trade and Investment, Adeniyi Adebayo, has said the Federal Government will continue to partner with all relevant stakeholders for infrastructural and economic development in the country. He stated this when officials from Oil and Gas Companies Cooperate Association of Nigeria led by the Secretary-General Zakari Kyari, visited him in Abuja. Adeniyi said there were two areas the association could partner with the ministry. The areas are setting up of Special Economic Zones and infrastructural development. He commended the association’s effort to provide affordable housing to Nigerians particularly in estate development in Abuja and Lekki in Lagos State. Copyright PUNCH.
